{"TopicId":138950,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"Terrain rendering performance","CreatedByName":"Teilnehmer","CreatedById":143330,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-04T14:31:25Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Teilnehmer","CreatedById":143330,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-04T14:31:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy configuration is:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nDesktop computer: Intel Core i5 3.2 GHz, 8 GB RAM, no discrete graphics card\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nOS: Windows 7 x64\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nKSP: 1.1.2 build 1260 x64 DirectX (the game crashes with OpenGL key)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nThe problem is when I set the \u003Cem\u003ERender quality\u003C/em\u003E parameter to at least \u003Cem\u003ESimple\u003C/em\u003E (even when all the other graphics parameters are minimal), the performance drops significantly (down to 4 fps). This happens only if there is some terrain in the frame. When it\u2019s the vessel and the sky only, the performance is OK.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u2019ve experienced nothing similar in 1.0.5.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I set \u003Cem\u003ERender quality\u003C/em\u003E to \u003Cem\u003EFast\u003C/em\u003E, everything performs normally. But I need at least \u003Cem\u003EGood\u003C/em\u003E to see cast shadows.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a solution?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-04T14:39:26Z\u0022 title=\u002205/04/2016 02:39  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 4, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Teilnehmer\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Padishar","CreatedById":97386,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-04T15:04:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222560690\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022138950\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462372285\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022143330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Teilnehmer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, Teilnehmer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a solution?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI presume you aren\u0027t looking for \u0022Buy a reasonable graphics card\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou could possibly try turning on the legacy shader stuff in the settings.cfg (you\u0027d need to search for the details and hope they weren\u0027t in the pre-release sub-forums that are now hidden \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E). \u00A0Also, the old tweaks to the ocean sub-division settings may also make a big difference...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Teilnehmer","CreatedById":143330,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-04T16:41:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222560749\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022138950\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462374267\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297386\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Padishar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Padishar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou could possibly try turning on the legacy shader stuff in the settings.cfg\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks a lot!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUNSUPPORTED_LEGACY_SHADER_TERRAIN = true\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat helped.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-04T17:08:01Z\u0022 title=\u002205/04/2016 05:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 4, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Teilnehmer\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"regex","CreatedById":70807,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-04T16:57:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis may also be of interest:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/138301-sm2-shaders-kopernicus-i-can-possibly-help/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}